## Fix 3: `ARRenderer.java` — Fix the "wobbles even after locked" bug

This is the real bug. Looking at `tryLock()` — once `b.locked = true` is set, `getMatrix()` correctly returns `b.lockedMatrix`. But the issue is **multi-point depth sampling was never added**, so the *initial* lock itself is based on noisy single-point hit-test data — it locks onto a wobbly position. Fix: average multiple hit-test points **before** starting the stability counter, not just rely on post-lock stability.

```java
// Replace placeBlocks() in ARRenderer.java with this version
// that samples MULTIPLE points and averages BEFORE locking begins

private void placeBlocks(QueuedPlacement q) {
    freeBlocks();

    for (TextBlock b : q.blocks) {
        if (b.translated == null || b.translated.isEmpty()) continue;

        float cx = (b.bitmapBounds.left + b.bitmapBounds.right)  / 2f;
        float cy = (b.bitmapBounds.top  + b.bitmapBounds.bottom) / 2f;
        float bw = b.bitmapBounds.width();
        float bh = b.bitmapBounds.height();

        // ── Multi-point hit-test: 5 points instead of 1 ─────────────────
        // Centre + 4 corners, inset 20% to stay inside the text region
        float insetX = bw * 0.2f;
        float insetY = bh * 0.2f;

        float[][] testPoints = {
            {cx, cy},                                          // centre
            {cx - bw/2f + insetX, cy - bh/2f + insetY},        // TL
            {cx + bw/2f - insetX, cy - bh/2f + insetY},        // TR
            {cx - bw/2f + insetX, cy + bh/2f - insetY},        // BL
            {cx + bw/2f - insetX, cy + bh/2f - insetY},        // BR
        };

        List<float[]> validHits  = new ArrayList<>(); // each: [x,y,z,depth]
        Plane          chosenPlane = null;
        float          totalDepth  = 0f;
        int            hitCount    = 0;

        for (float[] pt : testPoints) {
            try {
                List<HitResult> hits = q.frame.hitTest(pt[0], pt[1]);
                for (HitResult hit : hits) {
                    if (!(hit.getTrackable() instanceof Plane)) continue;
                    Plane plane = (Plane) hit.getTrackable();
                    if (plane.getTrackingState() != TrackingState.TRACKING) continue;
                    if (plane.getSubsumedBy() != null) continue;

                    float[] m = new float[16];
                    hit.getHitPose().toMatrix(m, 0);
                    validHits.add(new float[]{m[12], m[13], m[14], hit.getDistance()});
                    totalDepth += hit.getDistance();
                    hitCount++;
                    if (chosenPlane == null) chosenPlane = plane;
                    break; // first valid plane hit per point
                }
            } catch (Exception ignored) {}
        }

        Anchor anchor;
        float[] planeMatrix;
        float   depth;

        if (hitCount >= 2 && chosenPlane != null) {
            // ── Reject outliers: discard points >3cm from median position ──
            float[] avgPos = averagePosition(validHits);
            List<float[]> filtered = new ArrayList<>();
            for (float[] hit : validHits) {
                float dx = hit[0]-avgPos[0], dy = hit[1]-avgPos[1], dz = hit[2]-avgPos[2];
                float dist = (float)Math.sqrt(dx*dx+dy*dy+dz*dz);
                if (dist < 0.03f) filtered.add(hit);
            }
            if (filtered.isEmpty()) filtered = validHits; // fallback if all rejected

            float[] finalPos = averagePosition(filtered);
            depth = totalDepth / hitCount;

            // Build matrix: rotation from plane, translation = averaged position
            float[] pm = new float[16];
            chosenPlane.getCenterPose().toMatrix(pm, 0);

            planeMatrix = new float[]{
                pm[0], pm[1], pm[2],  0f,
                pm[4], pm[5], pm[6],  0f,
                pm[8], pm[9], pm[10], 0f,
                finalPos[0], finalPos[1], finalPos[2], 1f
            };

            try {
                Pose anchorPose = Pose.makeTranslation(
                    finalPos[0], finalPos[1], finalPos[2]);
                anchor = q.frame.getAndroidSensorPose() != null
                    ? session.createAnchor(anchorPose)
                    : null;
                if (anchor == null) anchor = session.createAnchor(anchorPose);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                anchor = null;
            }

        } else {
            // ── Fallback: not enough plane hits, use camera-forward placement
            depth = 0.6f;
            try {
                Pose camPose = q.frame.getCamera().getPose();
                float[] t   = camPose.getTranslation();
                float[] fwd = camPose.getZAxis();
                Pose pose   = Pose.makeTranslation(
                    t[0] - fwd[0] * depth,
                    t[1] - fwd[1] * depth,
                    t[2] - fwd[2] * depth);
                anchor = session.createAnchor(pose);
                planeMatrix = new float[16];
                pose.toMatrix(planeMatrix, 0);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                continue; // skip this block entirely
            }
        }

        if (anchor == null) continue;

        // ── Real-world size from averaged depth ─────────────────────────
        float tanHalfFov  = 0.577f;
        float screenFracW = bw / q.viewW;
        float screenFracH = bh / q.viewH;
        b.widthM  = Math.max(0.04f, Math.min(3f, 2f * depth * tanHalfFov * screenFracW));
        b.heightM = Math.max(0.02f, Math.min(2f, 2f * depth * tanHalfFov * screenFracH));

        // ── Upload texture ────────────────────────────────────────────────
        Bitmap bmp = OverlayBitmap.create(b);
        int[] tex  = new int[1];
        GLES20.glGenTextures(1, tex, 0);
        GLES20.glBindTexture(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D, tex[0]);
        GLES20.glTexParameteri(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D,
            GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_MIN_FILTER, GLES20.GL_LINEAR_MIPMAP_LINEAR);
        GLES20.glTexParameteri(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D,
            GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_MAG_FILTER, GLES20.GL_LINEAR);
        GLES20.glTexParameteri(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D,
            GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_S, GLES20.GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE);
        GLES20.glTexParameteri(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D,
            GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_WRAP_T, GLES20.GL_CLAMP_TO_EDGE);
        GLUtils.texImage2D(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D, 0, bmp, 0);
        GLES20.glGenerateMipmap(GLES20.GL_TEXTURE_2D);
        bmp.recycle();

        b.glTexture   = tex[0];
        b.anchor      = anchor;
        b.planeMatrix = planeMatrix;

        // ── Pre-seed lockedMatrix from the averaged position immediately ──
        // This means tryLock() starts from a STABLE point, not a noisy one
        float[] anchorM = new float[16];
        anchor.getPose().toMatrix(anchorM, 0);
        float[] seedMatrix = planeMatrix.clone();
        seedMatrix[12] = anchorM[12];
        seedMatrix[13] = anchorM[13];
        seedMatrix[14] = anchorM[14];
        b.lockedMatrix = seedMatrix;

        blocks.add(b);
    }
}

private float[] averagePosition(List<float[]> hits) {
    float x=0,y=0,z=0;
    for (float[] h : hits) { x+=h[0]; y+=h[1]; z+=h[2]; }
    int n = hits.size();
    return new float[]{x/n, y/n, z/n};
}
```

And critically — fix `tryLock()` so once locked it is **truly immutable**, with an extra safety check that prevents any code path from touching `lockedMatrix` after `locked=true`:

```java
// Replace tryLock() in ARRenderer.java

private void tryLock(TextBlock b, float[] current) {
    if (b.locked) return; // SAFETY: never re-enter once locked

    if (b.stableFrames == 0 && b.lockedMatrix != null) {
        // First frame — already seeded in placeBlocks(), just start counting
        b.stableFrames = 1;
        return;
    }

    float dx = current[12] - b.lockedMatrix[12];
    float dy = current[13] - b.lockedMatrix[13];
    float dz = current[14] - b.lockedMatrix[14];
    float drift = (float) Math.sqrt(dx*dx + dy*dy + dz*dz);

    if (drift < LOCK_DRIFT) {
        b.stableFrames++;
        // Slowly converge lockedMatrix toward current (low-pass filter)
        // instead of snapping — eliminates micro-jitter in the final lock
        float blend = 0.1f;
        b.lockedMatrix[12] += (current[12] - b.lockedMatrix[12]) * blend;
        b.lockedMatrix[13] += (current[13] - b.lockedMatrix[13]) * blend;
        b.lockedMatrix[14] += (current[14] - b.lockedMatrix[14]) * blend;
    } else {
        b.stableFrames = Math.max(0, b.stableFrames - 5); // penalise big jumps harder
    }

    if (b.stableFrames >= LOCK_FRAMES) {
        b.locked = true;
        if (b.anchor != null) {
            b.anchor.detach();
            b.anchor = null;
        }
    }
}
```

And in `getMatrix()`, add the same safety so a locked block's matrix is **never reassigned** by accident elsewhere in the draw loop:

```java
private float[] getMatrix(TextBlock b) {
    if (b.locked) {
        return b.lockedMatrix; // returned by reference — never mutated after lock
    }

    if (b.anchor == null ||
        b.anchor.getTrackingState() != TrackingState.TRACKING) {
        return b.lockedMatrix;
    }

    float[] anchorM = new float[16];
    b.anchor.getPose().toMatrix(anchorM, 0);

    // IMPORTANT: don't mutate b.lockedMatrix here — return a NEW array
    // Previously this may have been aliasing the same array as lockedMatrix
    float[] m = b.planeMatrix.clone();
    m[12] = anchorM[12];
    m[13] = anchorM[13];
    m[14] = anchorM[14];
    return m;
}
