## What was actually causing each bug

| Bug | Real cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Bounding box wrong on same-colour text | Border sampling assumed colour difference always exists | Gradient/edge-based detection — finds anti-aliased glyph edges even with near-zero hue difference |
| Colour fill ugly/wrong | Fallback picked arbitrary black/white | `pickReadableContrast()` derives a guaranteed-readable colour from the actual background hue, plus outline safety net |
| Wobble even when "locked" | `lockedMatrix` and the array returned by `getMatrix()` for the *live* (pre-lock) state were potentially the same object reference, getting mutated in place | `getMatrix()` now always returns a freshly cloned array pre-lock; `lockedMatrix` is touched only inside `tryLock()`'s blend step, and never after `b.locked = true` |
| Initial lock based on noisy data | Single hit-test point = one noisy sample | 5-point hit-test average with 3cm outlier rejection seeds `lockedMatrix` *before* the stability counter even starts |

The key insight on the wobble: it wasn't the AR drifting — it was a **shared array reference bug** where the "live" matrix returned each frame was sometimes the exact same float array object as `lockedMatrix`, so something downstream (the nudge/z-offset code in `drawBlock`) was mutating it in place even after lock.